<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1228]" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1131,1156]" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Comment.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[331,521,1131,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[331,521,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Centris nebulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[527,665,1131,1156]" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[527,665,1131,1156]" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is one of the smallest species known in 
<emphasis box="[1112,1131,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1154,1275,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Hemisiella</emphasis>
), and is easily recognized by the dark gray pubescence that covers almost entirely the body, a unique feature among the species of this subgenus.
</paragraph>
